Background: 19yo Female. 5ft. 108lbs. Born with neurofibromatosis. Reason for MRI was increased migraines due to the birth control I was taking. They have gone down since stopping the birth control but I still get occasional migraines. 

My MRI results are as follows: (I don't know what these terms really mean) Small rounded T1 and T2 hyperintense foci within right corpus callous splenium(0.8×0.5 cm) and right inferior basal ganglia(0.6×0.5 cm) No hemorrhage. Left middle cranial fossa small arachnoid cyst(1.5×0.7 cm) No midline shift.
